    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "The window geometry and position for Neovim should be remembered for a specific file. A new file  should use a default.\r\n\r\nIt's somewhat annoying to have to always resize the editor window whenever I open a file, so If I have resized a window for a file, the next time I open that file,  Neovim  should go back to its previous window size.\r\n\r\nAs I am on Ubuntu, this may be an issue related to ubuntu or gnome-terminal itself and not neovim. Please let me know.\r\n\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "The first issue is solved by this snippets. There are other variants floating around and probably also sophisticated plugins, which solve this issue elegantly. Vim does have a variation of this snippet in its `default.vim`, which is loaded, when no `.vimrc` is found, IIRC. \r\nNeovim does not include this snippet by default though. \r\n\r\n```vim\r\n\" save last cursor poistion at \\ mark and open buffer at last cursor position\r\naugroup LastCursorPos\r\n    autocmd!\r\n    autocmd BufReadPost * if @% !~# \"\\.git[\\/\\\\]COMMIT_EDITMSG$\" && line(\"'\\\"\") > 1 && line(\"'\\\"\") <= line(\"$\") | exe \"normal! g`\\\"\" | endif\r\naugroup end\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe second problem can be tackled via `:help session` and tpopes wonderfull [`vim-obsession`](https://github.com/tpope/vim-obsession) plugin. ",
